    "created_at": "2014-07-04T12:16:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-04T12:16:40Z",
    "body": "`App.getHomeDir()` doesn't align with the OS X guidelines of storing application data. These files should be put in `~/Library/Application Support/YourApp` or `/Library/Application Support/YourApp` for shared users.`App.getHomeDir()` will give you `/Users/<username>` on OS X -- not the right place to store application support files.\nTherefore, on OS X you can \"build\" `dataPath` on your own:\n`var dataPath = App.getHomeDir() + \"/Library/Application Support/\" + appName;`\nTake care that the directory exists.\n"
  },
